<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#00ff00" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">a_random_lurker00</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ok, here's my situation: After first downloading DXwindows, I installed it. Had problems due to desktop rez mixups. Fixed that, DXwindows worked 100% perfectly fine. I haven't even TOUCHED Everquest for the last 4 weeks. Now, after the latest patch, I start DXwindows, Start EQ, log in, get to the char select screen, choose a character, wait.. and... Error message, Everquest closed. Argh! I honestly haven't messed with my system configuration at all, and it just stopped working :\<P>Interestingly, due to some OTHER graphics changes they put in, I can't really play Everquest without DXwindows: If my Desktop Rez and EQ Rez are NOT synched, and I run Everquest without Dxwindows, I get constant, horrendous, migraine-inducing flickering in my spellbook screen. Since I customarily run in 1152 res, this causes problems. With DXWindows running, I can control everything, AND be able to play normally. <P>So, did Verant break DXWindows for anyone else, or did my system just go apeshit?<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ashran</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Still working fine for me, the next version should be out on monday tho</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">bilj</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ashran, <P>And may I say how sweet a proggie you got here in dxwindows.<P>Can't wait till monday.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">a_mage0</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">/cheer again</FONT